We know that Gissela's truck carries 4,000 pounds of gravel (x=4000). We also understand that Gordy’s truck carries 800 pounds more than what Gissela's truck carries which means it holds ((4*0+8)*1) i.e., 800 pounds extra making up to x + 800 = 4800. When we add these amounts together along with Gary's amount, let g denote Gary's capacity ,we get 4000(gissela)+ 4800(gordy)+g(gary)=  11600 . Simplifying this equation leads us to solve as follows; 
Substituting values into our derived formula yields :

\[ (x_g)(x_g + 800) + x_g = 11600 \] Subtract \( x_g \) from both sides : \[ (x_g)^2 + 800 \cdot x_g = 11600\] Adding brackets makes life easier ; divide through by one
